Text: Women should be able to make their own health care choices. Period.
It’s pretty simple: passing Build Back Better saves Americans money. It cuts costs on everything from prescriptions to childcare. That’s a big deal!

Like President Biden said yesterday in Minnesota: We need to train the next generation of workers to do the jobs that are out there. Jobs in construction, fixing electric cars, plumbers, and electricians. That’s what our infrastructure bill and Build Back Better invest in.

The Supreme Court could fundamentally change what rights women have in this country.

We can’t go backward, we must write Roe into law.

Tomorrow, the Supreme Court will hear arguments in a case that is fundamentally about a woman’s right to choose. We cannot go back. We have a chance to write Roe v. Wade into law, we have got to take it.

Voting rights are fundamental to our democracy. We need to restore the rules of the Senate, pass the Freedom to Vote Act, and protect access to the ballot box.

We have a shortage of health care workers. We have a shortage of plumbers, electricians, and construction workers. We have workforce issues and our country needs more apprenticeships  and workforce training. That’s why Build Back Better is so important.
Big pharma doesn’t need help, seniors do. Congress needs to lift the ban on Medicare negotiating for lower prescription costs. Let’s get it done.
Ask any family and they’ll tell you that if you can’t afford child care, you can’t work. It’s time to cut working families a break.
